olive oil
1 cucumber
1 avocado
½ lemon
1 packet parsley
1 packet haloumi/grill cheese
1 courgette
2 tbs milk
½ cup plain flour
1 sachet Classic Roast Seasoning
1 egg
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves

• Slice cucumber into half-moons.
• Slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and roughly chop.
• Zest lemon to get a pinch and slice into wedges.
• Finely chop parsley.
• Grate halloumi and courgette. Squeeze any excess moisture out of the courgette using a paper towel.

TIP: Squeezing out the excess moisture from the courgette ensures your fritter batter is the right consistency.

• In a medium bowl, combine halloumi, courgette, lemon zest, parsley, the milk, plain flour, classic roast seasoning, the egg and a pinch of salt and pepper.

TIP: Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon. If it's too wet and doesn’t hold its shape, add a little more flour!

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, add heaped tablespoons of fritter mixture in batches and flatten with a spatula (5-6 per person).
• Cook until golden, 3-4 minutes each side (don't flip too early!). Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Add extra olive oil between batches as needed.

• In a second medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, cucumber, avocado, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.
• Divide avo salad between bowls.
• Top with courgette-halloumi fritters.
• Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!